  "text": "The Kubernetes CRD validation schema to OpenAPI schema publishing chain involves the following key components:\n\n**1. CRD Validation Specification (Entry Point)**\nCustomResourceDefinition resources contain a CustomResourceValidation field (defined in staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types.go and the internal version in staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/types.go). The CustomResourceValidation type includes an OpenAPIV3Schema field of type JSONSchemaProps that holds the actual validation schema.\n\n**2. Structural Schema Extraction**\nThe JSONSchemaProps from the CRD validation spec is converted to a Structural schema type via the NewStructural function (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/convert.go:42). This function recursively converts the JSONSchemaProps into the internal Structural representation, which is defined in staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/structural.go:27. The Structural type contains nested Properties, Items, AdditionalProperties, along with Generic, Extensions, and ValidationExtensions fields that capture Kubernetes-specific OpenAPI v3 vendor extensions.\n\n**3. OpenAPI Schema Conversion**\nThe Structural schema is converted back to go-openapi spec.Schema format via the ToKubeOpenAPI method (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/kubeopenapi.go:24). This method is faithful and roundtrippable, preserving all schema information. The ToKubeOpenAPI method outputs a spec.Schema with all generic fields, extensions, and validation rules intact. Additionally, ConvertJSONSchemaProps (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/validation/validation.go:236) provides an alternative conversion path.\n\n**4. OpenAPI V3 Schema Building**\nThe BuildOpenAPIV3 function (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go:194) orchestrates the creation of complete OpenAPI v3 specifications from CRD definitions. This function uses the builder type (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go:232) which contains the converted schema and generates a WebService that kube-openapi can consume. The builder creates both resource and list kind schemas and invokes builder3.BuildOpenAPISpecFromRoutes to generate the final spec3.OpenAPI object.\n\n**5. OpenAPI V3 Controller and Publishing**\nThe openapiv3.Controller (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go:46) watches CustomResourceDefinition changes and publishes OpenAPI v3 specifications. The controller's Run method (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go:85) receives an OpenAPIService and maintains specs per GroupVersion and CRD name. It listens for CRD add/update/delete events and triggers spec rebuilding via the sync function.\n\n**6. API Server Endpoint Registration**\nThe API server integration happens in staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/apiserver.go (lines 237-240), where the OpenAPI v3 controller is instantiated and run with the OpenAPIV3VersionedService. The endpoint installation is handled by InstallV3 (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/openapi.go:53), which registers the /openapi/v3 endpoint and /openapi/v3/<groupversion> versioned endpoints. The OpenAPIService from kube-openapi/pkg/handler3 handles the actual HTTP serving.\n\n**7. Supporting Infrastructure**\nThe customresource_handler (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_handler.go) uses the structural schemas for validation and pruning. When a CRD is registered, the handler creates the necessary validators and defaulters using the extracted Structural schema. The v2 conversion layer (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/v2/conversion.go) provides compatibility with OpenAPI v2 clients.\n\nThis chain ensures that CRD validation schemas are properly extracted, converted, and published as discoverable OpenAPI v3 specifications that clients can use to understand the API structure and validate resources."
